6.","meanings":["From the French form of Latin or Italian  <b>Carolina</b> , a feminine derivative of <i>Carolus</i> (  see  Charles  ). This name was used by certain gentry families from the 17th century onwards, no doubt in honour of the Stuart kings named <i>Charles</i>. It was famously borne by  Lady Caroline Lamb  (  1785–1828 ), mistress of the poet  Lord Byron ."],"variants":[{"name":"Carolyn","meanings":["Altered form of   Caroline ."]}]},{"name":"Ann","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Anne .  In the U.S. <i>Ann</i> is the more frequent spelling."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":3,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":12,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705195,"age":57,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Lady Caroline Ann Garvays was born in 1325, in Briercliffe, Lancashire, England, her father, Baron Robert John Garvays, was 25 and her mother, Baroness Avery Markham, was 25. She married John Carri